\begin_layout Subsection*
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This policy establishes the formal governance structure,
 methodology,
 and responsibilities for managing information technology risk within Elko County.
 It mandates a lifecycle approach to identifying,
 assessing,
 responding to,
 and monitoring risks that threaten the confidentiality,
 integrity,
 and availability of County information systems.
 This policy serves as the authority for risk-based decision-making,
 resource prioritization,
 and the formal acceptance of operational risk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This policy applies to all information systems,
 infrastructure,
 data,
 personnel,
 and third-party vendors managed by or on behalf of the Elko County Information Operations Department.
 It governs strategic,
 operational,
 compliance,
 and technical risk throughout the system development lifecycle (SDLC)
\end_layout

